{
  "page": "Marcher lords",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Bryce_Caron_by_quickreaver.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/87/Bryce_Caron_by_quickreaver.jpg/350px-Bryce_Caron_by_quickreaver.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"314\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/87/Bryce_Caron_by_quickreaver.jpg/525px-Bryce_Caron_by_quickreaver.jpg 1.5x, /images/8/87/Bryce_Caron_by_quickreaver.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Bryce_Caron_by_quickreaver.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Bryce_Caron\" title=\"Bryce Caron\">Bryce Caron</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_the_Marches\" title=\"Lord of the Marches\">Lord of the Marches</a>, by Quickreaver © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Marcher lords</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> (alternatively <b>marcher lords</b> in lowercase)<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> are <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lords</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">stormlands</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a> who live within the <a href=\"/index.php/Dornish_Marches\" title=\"Dornish Marches\">Dornish Marches</a>. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Culture\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Culture</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Marcher_lords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Marcher lords</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Culture\">Culture</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Marcher_lords&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Culture\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Marcher lords have proudly defended the realms of the <a href=\"/index.php/Storm_Kings\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Storm Kings\">Storm Kings</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Kings_of_the_Reach\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kings of the Reach\">Kings of the Reach</a> against incursions from <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_the_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_the_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Many ballads and tales praise the valor and skill at arms of the Marcher lords and their longbowmen.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_the_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_the_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/House_Caron\" title=\"House Caron\">House Caron</a> uses the title <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_the_Marches\" title=\"Lord of the Marches\">Lord of the Marches</a>, although they do not hold dominion over the other marcher houses of the stormlands. The Carons and the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Swann\" title=\"House Swann\">Swanns</a> both claim to be the oldest of the marcher lords.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_the_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_the_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Marcher_lords\">Marcher lords</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Marcher_lords&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Marcher lords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Caron\" title=\"House Caron\"><img alt=\"House Caron.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/6d/House_Caron.svg/32px-House_Caron.svg.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"35\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/6d/House_Caron.svg/48px-House_Caron.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/6d/House_Caron.svg/64px-House_Caron.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/House_Caron\" title=\"House Caron\">House Caron</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Nightsong\" title=\"Nightsong\">Nightsong</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> (deposed)</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Dondarrion\" title=\"House Dondarrion\"><img alt=\"House Dondarrion.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/ad/House_Dondarrion.svg/32px-House_Dondarrion.svg.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"35\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/ad/House_Dondarrion.svg/48px-House_Dondarrion.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/ad/House_Dondarrion.svg/64px-House_Dondarrion.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/House_Dondarrion\" title=\"House Dondarrion\">House Dondarrion</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Blackhaven\" title=\"Blackhaven\">Blackhaven</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Foote_of_Nightsong\" title=\"House Foote of Nightsong\"><img alt=\"None.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/58/None.svg/32px-None.svg.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"35\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/58/None.svg/48px-None.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/58/None.svg/64px-None.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/House_Foote_of_Nightsong\" title=\"House Foote of Nightsong\">House Foote</a>  of <a href=\"/index.php/Nightsong\" title=\"Nightsong\">Nightsong</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> (recently)</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Peake\" title=\"House Peake\"><img alt=\"House Peake.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b2/House_Peake.svg/32px-House_Peake.svg.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"35\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b2/House_Peake.svg/48px-House_Peake.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b2/House_Peake.svg/64px-House_Peake.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/House_Peake\" title=\"House Peake\">House Peake</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Starpike\" title=\"Starpike\">Starpike</a> (possibly)<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Selmy\" title=\"House Selmy\"><img alt=\"House Selmy.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/ec/House_Selmy.svg/32px-House_Selmy.svg.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"35\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/ec/House_Selmy.svg/48px-House_Selmy.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/ec/House_Selmy.svg/64px-House_Selmy.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/House_Selmy\" title=\"House Selmy\">House Selmy</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Harvest_Hall\" title=\"Harvest Hall\">Harvest Hall</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Swann\" title=\"House Swann\"><img alt=\"House Swann.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/94/House_Swann.svg/32px-House_Swann.svg.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"35\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/94/House_Swann.svg/48px-House_Swann.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/94/House_Swann.svg/64px-House_Swann.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/House_Swann\" title=\"House Swann\">House Swann</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Stonehelm\" title=\"Stonehelm\">Stonehelm</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Tarly\" title=\"House Tarly\"><img alt=\"House Tarly.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/cc/House_Tarly.svg/32px-House_Tarly.svg.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"35\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/cc/House_Tarly.svg/48px-House_Tarly.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/cc/House_Tarly.svg/64px-House_Tarly.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tarly\" title=\"House Tarly\">House Tarly</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Horn_Hill\" title=\"Horn Hill\">Horn Hill</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aenys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aenys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/32px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"35\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/48px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/64px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> The <a href=\"/index.php/Prince_of_Summerhall\" title=\"Prince of Summerhall\">Prince of Summerhall</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> (historically)</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Marcher_lords&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In <a href=\"/index.php/10_AC\" title=\"10 AC\">10&#160;AC</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Dornish_War\" title=\"First Dornish War\">First Dornish War</a>, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/House_Fowler\" title=\"House Fowler\">Fowler</a> surprised the unsuspecting marcher lords by quickly raiding the <a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a> and capturing <a href=\"/index.php/Nightsong\" title=\"Nightsong\">Nightsong</a>. Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Addam_Hightower\" title=\"Addam Hightower\">Addam Hightower</a> responded by marching from <a href=\"/index.php/Oldtown\" title=\"Oldtown\">Oldtown</a> to retake Nightsong, but while he was gone Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Dayne\" title=\"Joffrey Dayne\">Joffrey Dayne</a> burned the environs of Oldtown. The Fowlers had meanwhile burned Nightsong and fled into the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Mountains\" title=\"Red Mountains\">Red Mountains</a> with captive <a href=\"/index.php/House_Caron\" title=\"House Caron\">Carons</a>. Addam returned to Oldtown to confront Joffrey, but the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Dayne\" title=\"House Dayne\">Daynes</a> had by then also fled back to the mountains of <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>After ascending the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/37_AC\" title=\"37 AC\">37&#160;AC</a>, King <a href=\"/index.php/Aenys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aenys I Targaryen\">Aenys I Targaryen</a> visited the marcher lords in their castles during his journey to Oldtown. When <a href=\"/index.php/Dornishmen\" title=\"Dornishmen\">Dornishmen</a> began raiding the Marches in the <a href=\"/index.php/Second_Dornish_War\" title=\"Second Dornish War\">Second Dornish War</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Orys_Baratheon\" title=\"Orys Baratheon\">Orys Baratheon</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Paramount_of_the_Stormlands\" title=\"Lord Paramount of the Stormlands\">Lord Paramount of the Stormlands</a>, responded by smashing Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Walter_Wyl\" title=\"Walter Wyl\">Walter Wyl</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Stonehelm\" title=\"Stonehelm\">Stonehelm</a>. Nightsong resisted a siege by the <a href=\"/index.php/Vulture_King_(Aenys_I)\" title=\"Vulture King (Aenys I)\">Vulture King</a>, and the bandit leader's host was then destroyed by Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Ellyn_Caron\" title=\"Ellyn Caron\">Ellyn Caron</a>, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Harmon_Dondarrion\" title=\"Harmon Dondarrion\">Harmon Dondarrion</a>, and Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Samwell_Tarly_(lord)\" title=\"Samwell Tarly (lord)\">Samwell Tarly</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Vulture_Hunt\" title=\"Vulture Hunt\">Vulture Hunt</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Lords <a href=\"/index.php/House_Dondarrion\" title=\"House Dondarrion\">Dondarrion</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Selmy\" title=\"House Selmy\">Selmy</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tarly\" title=\"House Tarly\">Tarly</a> represented the Dornish Marches at the <a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Wedding\" title=\"Golden Wedding\">Golden Wedding</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/49_AC\" title=\"49 AC\">49&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> King <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a> visited <a href=\"/index.php/Horn_Hill\" title=\"Horn Hill\">Horn Hill</a>, Nightsong, and <a href=\"/index.php/Blackhaven\" title=\"Blackhaven\">Blackhaven</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/54_AC\" title=\"54 AC\">54&#160;AC</a> after the elevation of <a href=\"/index.php/Alfyn\" title=\"Alfyn\">Alfyn</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/High_Septon\" title=\"High Septon\">High Septon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> In <a href=\"/index.php/61_AC\" title=\"61 AC\">61&#160;AC</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Third_Dornish_War\" title=\"Third Dornish War\">Third Dornish War</a>, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Simon_Dondarrion\" title=\"Simon Dondarrion\">Simon Dondarrion</a> led a small force of marcher knights into the western Red Mountains against a <a href=\"/index.php/Vulture_King_(Jaehaerys_I)\" title=\"Vulture King (Jaehaerys I)\">second Vulture King</a>, and Jaehaerys and Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Rogar_Baratheon\" title=\"Rogar Baratheon\">Rogar Baratheon</a> pursued the outlaws from the east.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Marcher lords attended the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Council_of_101_AC\" title=\"Great Council of 101 AC\">Great Council of 101 AC</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>King <a href=\"/index.php/Maekar_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maekar I Targaryen\">Maekar I Targaryen</a> was slain fighting a rebellious lord on the Dornish Marches<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_maekar_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_maekar_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Peake_Uprising\" title=\"Peake Uprising\">Peake Uprising</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Marcher_lords&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Marcher_lords&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Francisco_Rico_Torres_Randyll_Tarly.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/9b/Francisco_Rico_Torres_Randyll_Tarly.JPG/350px-Francisco_Rico_Torres_Randyll_Tarly.JPG\" width=\"350\" height=\"226\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/9b/Francisco_Rico_Torres_Randyll_Tarly.JPG/525px-Francisco_Rico_Torres_Randyll_Tarly.JPG 1.5x, /images/9/9b/Francisco_Rico_Torres_Randyll_Tarly.JPG 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Francisco_Rico_Torres_Randyll_Tarly.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Randyll_Tarly\" title=\"Randyll Tarly\">Randyll Tarly</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Horn_Hill\" title=\"Lord of Horn Hill\">Lord of Horn Hill</a>, by Francisco Rico Torres © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a>, acting <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a>, arranges a betrothal between his niece, Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Myrcella_Baratheon\" title=\"Myrcella Baratheon\">Myrcella Baratheon</a>, and Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Trystane_Martell\" title=\"Trystane Martell\">Trystane Martell</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Five_Kings\" title=\"War of the Five Kings\">War of the Five Kings</a>. Trystane's father <a href=\"/index.php/Doran_Martell\" title=\"Doran Martell\">Doran</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Prince_of_Dorne\" title=\"Prince of Dorne\">Prince of Dorne</a>, fortifies the high passes of the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Mountains\" title=\"Red Mountains\">Red Mountains</a> to prevent the Marcher lords from aiding King <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok49.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_18-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok49.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-18\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Philip_Foote\" title=\"Philip Foote\">Philip Foote</a> kills the last <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Nightsong\" title=\"Lord of Nightsong\">Lord of Nightsong</a>, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Bryce_Caron\" title=\"Bryce Caron\">Bryce Caron</a>, in single combat during the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Blackwater\" title=\"Battle of the Blackwater\">Battle of the Blackwater</a>. He is awarded the lands, rights and incomes of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Caron\" title=\"House Caron\">House Caron</a> as a reward by the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a>, founding <a href=\"/index.php/House_Foote_of_Nightsong\" title=\"House Foote of Nightsong\">House Foote of Nightsong</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Marcher_lords&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Angry at the death of her father, <a href=\"/index.php/Oberyn_Martell\" title=\"Oberyn Martell\">Oberyn Martell</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Obara_Sand\" title=\"Obara Sand\">Obara Sand</a> wants to lead an army from the <a href=\"/index.php/Prince%27s_Pass\" title=\"Prince&#39;s Pass\">Prince's Pass</a> against the marcher lords and then <a href=\"/index.php/Oldtown\" title=\"Oldtown\">Oldtown</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Marcher_lords&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The Marcher lords are duly proud of their history as key defenders of <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">the realm</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Storm_King\" title=\"Storm King\">Storm Kings</a>, and many are the ballads and tales of their valor.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_the_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_the_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;writings of <a href=\"/index.php/Yandel\" title=\"Yandel\">Yandel</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Tyrion</b>: Any chance we might convince the <a href=\"/index.php/Dornishmen\" title=\"Dornishmen\">Dornishmen</a> to descend on the <a href=\"/index.php/Dornish_Marches\" title=\"Dornish Marches\">Marches</a>?<br />\n</p><p><b>Varys</b>: None.<br />\n</p>\n<b>Tyrion</b>: A pity. Well, the threat may serve to keep the Marcher lords close to their castles, at least.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Varys\" title=\"Varys\">Varys</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Marcher_lords&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">According to the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.historyofwesteros.com/concarolinas-westerlands-reading/\">ConCarolinas westerlands reading</a>, King <a href=\"/index.php/Maekar_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maekar I Targaryen\">Maekar I Targaryen</a> was slain at <a href=\"/index.php/Starpike\" title=\"Starpike\">Starpike</a>, while <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> states Maekar was killed on the Dornish Marches.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Marcher_lords&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones-Chapter_29\" title=\"A Game of Thrones-Chapter 29\">Chapter 29</a>, Sansa II.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">